This paper deals with the security of deep neural networks (DNNs) used for malware detection, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also involves optimization techniques to manipulate binary code, which is related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the evaluation of different defenses, which is related to software engineering (cs.SE) and systems and control (cs.SY).
